    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="509"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d509">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.91/1–1145</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Director of the Office of Near Eastern wad
                        African Affairs</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-30">December 30,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I concur fully that it would be preferable for the matter of the Iranian Railway
                    and free port to be discussed with the President, and I hope you will have an
                    early opportunity to do so. I am afraid, if the matter is delayed, that the
                    President may feel that adequate attention is not being paid to his suggestion
                    that Harriman take up the matter with Stalin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wallace Murray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
